-- Brooklyn Nets Defeat Hornets for Fourth Win in Five NBA Games
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-03-13T04:00:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-13/brooklyn-nets-defeat-hornets-for-fourth-win-in-five-nba-games.html
Brook Lopez scored 26 points to
lead the Brooklyn Nets to a 108-98 victory over the New Orleans
Hornets.  A fourth win in five National Basketball Association games
lifted the Nets to 38-27, two games behind the New York Knicks,
who lead Eastern Conference’s five-team Atlantic Division with a
38-23 mark.  Deron Williams  had 21 points and 13 assists, and reserve
Andray Blatche added 18 points for the Nets, who had a 57-48
halftime lead on their home court at Barclays Center.  Eric Gordon scored 24 points and  Anthony Davis  had 17
points and 11 rebounds for the Hornets (22-43), who are last in
the Western Conference’s Southwest Division, 27 games behind the
San Antonio Spurs (49-15).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
